A Cluster is a group of patients with the same disease who are grouped by one or more properties that are considered critical to an analysis of how the disease has spread.
indicate a medical condition existing simultaneously but independently with another condition in a patient (source: Wikipedia)

A cluster defined by contact with certain individuals. Note that to some extent all clusters are contact clusters so this class is used only for those clusters that specifically mention contact with individuals (or lack of knowledge about such contact) rather than geographic, time, or disease data.

Coronaviruses are a large family of viruses which may cause illness in animals or humans.  In humans, several coronaviruses are known to cause respiratory infections ranging from the common cold to more severe diseases such as Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) and Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS). (source: https://www.who.int/news-room/q-a-detail/q-a-coronaviruses)
Any facility, such as hotels/lodges/hostels/stadiums for providing care to COVID-19 patients are reffered as Covid Care Centre (CCC).
The Dedicated COVID Health Centre are hospitals that shall offer care for all cases that have been clinically assigned as moderate.
The Dedicated COVID Hospitals are hospitals that shall offer comprehensive care primarily for those who have been clinically assigned as severe.
A person diagnosed With COVID-19.

A union territory ('Federally administered territory/province') is a type of administrative division in the Republic of India. Unlike the states of India, which have their own governments, union territories are federal territories governed directly by the Central Government of India.

An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.
